In a message dated 1/13/2007 3:18:26 A.M. Eastern Standard Time,
terryyoesting@... writes:

have been wanting to know what some of the abbreviations you are using
mean. Such as dd, ds, dh, IMO (in my opinion?)



dd=dear daughter or darling daughter
ds=dear son or darling son
dh=dear husband or darling husband
IMO does indeed mean "in my opinion"

HTH
(tee hee...couldn't resist that one, which, by the way, means hope this
helps)

Wendy in Homestead, FL
